      • requestAlbumByUPC

        public static DeezerRequest requestAlbumByUPC(String upc)
        Requests an album informations based on the UPC (Universal Product Code). The UPC is usually a 12 digits number, corresponding to the album's barcode. Note that a single album may have different UPC number depending on countries and editions.


        Note that if the ISRC doesn't match any track in Deezer's catalog, this request will generate a DeezerError

        Parameters:
        upc - the UPC of the album (eg: 724384960650).
        Returns:
        the DeezerRequest to fetch an album

      • requestTrackByISRC

        public static DeezerRequest requestTrackByISRC(String isrc)
        Requests a track information based on its ISRC (International Standard Recording Code). Each music track is given an ISRC code that is unique for a recording of a song. The ISRC code uses 12 alphanumeric characters


        Note that if the ISRC doesn't match any track in Deezer's catalog, this request will generate a DeezerError

        Parameters:
        isrc - the track's isrc (eg : CH3131340084).
        Returns:
        the DeezerRequest to fetch the info on the given track
